<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,1578,2037]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Coloration. Live coloration not known. Color of preserved specimens medium brown; head and belly darker than body, particularly opercle.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,1578,2037]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,1650,1676]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Discussion.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schwarzhans &amp; Møller" authorityYear="2021" box="[342,633,1650,1676]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" genus="Porogadus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="caboverdensis">
<emphasis box="[342,633,1650,1676]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Porogadus caboverdensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a typical member of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Goode &amp; Bean" authorityYear="1885" box="[960,1151,1650,1676]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" genus="Porogadus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="miles">
<emphasis box="[960,1151,1650,1676]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Porogadus miles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Group and resembles 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Goode &amp; Bean" authorityYear="1885" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" genus="Porogadus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="miles">P. miles</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Garman" authorityYear="1899" box="[226,365,1686,1712]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" genus="Porogadus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longiceps">P. longiceps</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Schwarzhans &amp; Møller, 2021" authorityName="Schwarzhans &amp; Møller" authorityYear="2021" box="[377,493,1686,1712]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" genus="Porogadus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mendax" status="n. sp.">P. mendax</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[502,566,1686,1712]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[502,566,1686,1712]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Schwarzhans &amp; Møller, 2021" authorityName="Schwarzhans &amp; Møller" authorityYear="2021" box="[581,775,1686,1712]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" genus="Porogadus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dracocephalus" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[581,775,1686,1712]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">P. dracocephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[783,848,1686,1712]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[783,848,1686,1712]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Schwarzhans &amp; Møller, 2021" authorityName="Schwarzhans &amp; Møller" authorityYear="2021" box="[912,1033,1686,1712]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" genus="Porogadus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="turgidus" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[912,1033,1686,1712]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">P. turgidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1042,1106,1686,1712]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1042,1106,1686,1712]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in the long and slender head (HL:HD&gt;1.75) and the many and intense spines on the head. It differs from 
<emphasis box="[1026,1264,1722,1748]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Goode &amp; Bean" authorityYear="1885" box="[1026,1116,1722,1748]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" genus="Porogadus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="miles">P. miles</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Garman" authorityYear="1899" box="[1128,1264,1722,1748]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" genus="Porogadus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longiceps">P. longiceps</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schwarzhans &amp; Møller" authorityYear="2021" box="[1321,1436,1722,1748]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" genus="Porogadus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mendax">
<emphasis box="[1321,1436,1722,1748]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">P. mendax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the lower number of lower lateral line pores until the beginning of the anal fin (16–19 vs 21–26), the narrow dentition on the vomer (1–3 rows, rarely 4 vs 3–7 rows, rarely 2) and the compressed otolith (OL:OH = 1.05–1.5 vs 1.7–2.0, rarely 1.6). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schwarzhans &amp; Møller" authorityYear="2021" box="[410,698,1830,1856]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" genus="Porogadus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="caboverdensis">
<emphasis box="[410,698,1830,1856]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Porogadus caboverdensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schwarzhans &amp; Møller" authorityYear="2021" box="[834,954,1830,1856]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" genus="Porogadus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="turgidus">
<emphasis box="[834,954,1830,1856]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">P. turgidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the narrow vomer (1–3, rarely 4 rows of teeth vs 4–7 rows) and in the single, uniform colliculum in the sulcus (vs separated colliculi). From 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schwarzhans &amp; Møller" authorityYear="2021" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" genus="Porogadus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dracocephalus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">P. dracocephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it differs in the wide palatines with 4–9 rows of teeth (vs 2–5 rows), the mostly higher preanal ratio (30.0–35.3 vs 28.6–30.6 % of SL) and the higher ratio OL:TCL of&gt;2.1 (vs &lt;2.0).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,1578,2037]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1974,2000]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schwarzhans &amp; Møller" authorityYear="2021" box="[362,652,1974,2000]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" genus="Porogadus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="caboverdensis">
<emphasis box="[362,652,1974,2000]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Porogadus caboverdensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a deep-water species that has only been caught below 
<quantity box="[1318,1405,1974,2001]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.4799999999999995" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" unit="m" value="4480.0">4480 m</quantity>
in the 
<collectingCountry box="[193,324,2010,2036]" name="Cape Verde" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Cape Verde</collectingCountry>
Basin off northwestern Africa, where it occurs together with two other deep-water species, i.e., 
<taxonomicName box="[1416,1437,2011,2036]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis box="[1416,1437,2011,2036]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">P.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
